[PLAY 3 S \HQ]
This is the heart finesse the extra trick rides on. Dummy leads the \H2 toward your hand, East follows low, and you hold \HAQ3 with the king still out. Which heart do you play?
[ACCEPT \H3]
[WHY]
Play the \HQ — the finesse. East followed low, so the \HK rates to sit under your A-Q just where you want it; the queen forces it out or wins outright, and the ace mops up the suit. Rising with the \HA instead gives back the free trick the finesse was set to win. Lead toward the A-Q and insert the queen — never bang the ace down first.}
