Lead the \D2. Fourth-best from your longest suit is the standard choice with no sequence available, and it tells partner about your length.

[ROLE declarer][STAGE auction-end]
You are in 2\H. Your trumps, diamonds and clubs build toward the eight tricks you need, and the \S suit, where you hold A and Q tight, is the one finesse spot that can win a trick if the \SK is missing. The plan is to draw trumps, develop diamonds, and take the spade finesse by leading toward your A-Q. NS hold 23 of the 40, so the defence has 17, and with neither opponent bidding no one is hiding a long suit or a big hand — the missing \SK rates to be split.

[ROLE declarer][STAGE post-lead]
