[PLAY 3 S \SQ]
Here is the spade finesse the partscore depends on. Dummy leads a low spade toward your hand, East follows low, and you hold \SAQ bare with the king still out. Which spade do you play?
[WHY]
Play the \SQ — the finesse. East followed low, so the \SK rates to sit under your A-Q, just where you want it, and the queen forces it out or wins outright. Play the \SA first instead and you make only one spade trick — your queen later falls to the king. Leading toward the A-Q and finessing the queen is how you make two, and it is the whole idea of a simple finesse.}
