[PLAY 5 S \SQ]
Here is the spade finesse for your ninth trick. Dummy leads the \S2 toward your hand and East plays the \ST, with you holding \SAQ4 and the king still out. Which spade do you play?
[WHY]
Play the \SQ — the finesse. The \ST cannot hurt you: East following with it leaves the \SK still sitting behind your A-Q, just where you want it, so the queen beats the ten and brings home the trick you need. Going up with the \SA instead leaves your lone queen to be swallowed by the king later — and with it the ninth trick. Cover nothing; lead toward the A-Q and slide the queen through.}
